==English==

===Etymology===
Latin ''mussātĭo'', ceasing to speak

===Noun===
{{en-noun}}

# [[speech]] conducted in a hushed manner, akin to a whisper or a murmur.
#*'''1989''', [[w:Nick Cave|Nick Cave]], ''[[w:And the Ass Saw the Angel|And the Ass Saw the Angel]]''
#*: The '''mussitation''' of the crowd dropped instantly.
# (''medical'') A comatose patient's action of forming words with his lips without producing sound.

